-- Turkey to Scrap 10% Withholding Tax on Income From Warrants, Minister Says
-- B y   E r c a n   E r s o y
-- 2010-09-28T06:26:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-28/turkey-to-scrap-10-withholding-tax-on-income-from-warrants-minister-says.html
Turkey plans to abolish the current
10 percent withholding tax in income from warrants, according to
a Finance Ministry document.  The draft proposal, shown to reporters in Istanbul today by
Finance Ministry officials, has been submitted to the Cabinet
for approval.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ercan Ersoy in Istanbul at 
 eersoy@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
